        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued March 26 at 4:56PM CDT by NWS Brownsville TX</headline>
        <description>At 455 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 8
miles southwest of Agua Nueva, moving northeast at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts up to 40 mph and half inch hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor hail damage to vegetation is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Puesta Del Sol Airport and Agua Nueva.
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.</instruction>
